<subSubSection pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="95.[151,1436,151,572]" box="[199,853,367,392]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,367,392]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[372,470,367,392]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species was not examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="95.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
The taxonomy of the genus is still unsatisfactory being the distinctive characters quite variable (see Bologna 1994). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1801" box="[231,352,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Synhoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testacea">
<emphasis box="[231,352,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">S. testacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems distributed only in southern Africa, but the differences with 
<emphasis box="[1120,1269,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">S. cephalotes</emphasis>
(Kolbe, 1897) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Laporte de Castelnau, 1840)" authorityName="Laporte de Castelnau" authorityYear="1840" baseAuthorityName="Laporte de Castelnau" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[200,714,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="senegalensis">
<emphasis box="[200,371,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">S. senegalensis</emphasis>
(Laporte de Castelnau, 1840)
</taxonomicName>
, both widely spread in the intertropical fascia of Africa, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">S. betsimirasaka</emphasis>
Paulian, 1956, from 
<collectingCountry box="[553,688,511,536]" name="Madagascar" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[747,848,512,536]" name="Comoros" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Comores</collectingCountry>
Islands, are not well defined (
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Laurenzi, M. (1994) Descriptions of the triungulins of Synhoria testacea (Fabricius) and of another undetermined African species (Coleoptera: Meloidae) with data on Horiini larvae. African Entomol o gy, 2, 155 - 162." type="journal article" year="1994">Bologna &amp; Laurenzi 1994</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
